mdRecord.dcterms:description: This is a paper, "The Willson-Walker House: A Provincial Neoclassical Revival Building," written by a student, Wayne Kille, for the Architecture 557 course (American Vernacular Architecture) taught by Dell Upton in Winter term 1980.
There is a copy of this paper in Collection 0294 -- Walker-Wood Family Papers, 1910-1975.
